{"actual_usd":0.12399,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":174,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24276,"reply":"\"No— not to Satan.\" *I rub a thumb along a dry streak of clay on my apron, thinking how often people make the enemy sound bigger than he is.* \"Scripture calls it a ransom because it cost something real to set us free, but it doesn't picture Jesus bargaining with the devil like two traders at market.\"\n\n*I shift against the bench and glance toward the window where the morning light keeps changing under the clouds.* \"If you want it plain: the payment is offered to God in the sense that Christ gave himself in obedience, justice is answered, sin is dealt with, and death is broken. Satan's not the rightful owner of anybody— he's a thief, not a lord collecting fees. The cross isn't God paying off a kidnapper. It's Christ defeating our enemies by giving himself for us.\"\n\n\"What brought that question on?\"","rolling_24h_usd":60.308285000000005,"run_id":"85f169a3-c48c-4f9d-af30-1f3d44921a46"}
